{{Quote|These cursed wretches are merely tribeless scavengers, not your proud T'Syriél.|Aron Peacebringer, to Kéral Longknife|<ref name="marvel53" />}}
The '''T'Syriél''' were tall, muscular [[Humanoid/Legends|humanoids]] native to the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Shiva IV]]. United into the [[Twelve Tribes of T'Syriél]], the T'Syriél were ancient rivals of the [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Calian Confederacy]], with which they warred for generations en route to building a strong and respected warrior tradition. In [[2 ABY/Legends|2 ABY]], those battles were brought to an end with the signing of the [[Concordat of Peace]], although many disaffected T'Syriél were used as troops by [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[General/Legends|General]] [[Bentilais san Sk'ar]]'s attempt to conquer the world.

==Biology and appearance==
Strong, tall and muscular, T'Syriél were bipedal [[Humanoid/Legends|humanoids]] native to the remote [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Shiva IV]]. T'Syriél had [[Color/Legends|orange]] skin and [[Dog/Legends|canine]] faces, and were often much larger than baseline [[Human/Legends|Humans]].<ref name="marvel53" />

==Society and culture==
{{Quote|I am ashamed, my brother. In happier times&mdash;before our two races signed the Concordat of Peace&mdash;a warrior of the 12 Tribes would die rather than flee from you nightskins.|Kéral Longknife, to Aron Peacebringer|<ref name="marvel53" />}}
During the era of the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], T'Syriél society was organized into the [[Twelve Tribes of T'Syriél]], which were led by a [[Demarch]]. However, there was a significant outcast population, consisting of T'Syriél who had largely organized themselves into bandit groups in the planet's wastes. The T'Syriél had a proud warrior tradition forged from generations of bloodshed, although that had started to decline somewhat by [[3 ABY]].<ref name="marvel53" />

==History==
{{Quote|Enormous stormtroopers!|[[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]], upon witnessing T'Syriél stormtroopers|<ref name="marvel53" />}}
For generations, the T'Syriél battled for supremacy on Shiva IV with the [[Human/Legends|Human]] population of the [[Calian Confederacy]], with the constant bloodshed turning the T'Syriél into fearsome warriors. However, that ended in [[2 ABY/Legends|2 ABY]], when Demarch [[Kéral Longknife]] signed the [[Concordat of Peace]] with [[Calian]] [[Warlord/Legends|Warlord]] [[Aron Peacebringer]], uniting the two peoples in friendship. That didn't solve all the problems that ailed the T'Syriél, however&mdash;in the months to come, many T'Syriél outcasts forgot their proud ways and lost the spirit that made them formidable warriors.<ref name="marvel53" />

In [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]], a number of T'Syriél outcasts were hired by [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[General]] [[Bentilais san Sk'ar]], a [[Kaleesh/Legends|Kaleesh]] who had been assigned to conquer Shiva IV in the Empire's name. In an effort to drive a wedge in between the Twelve Tribes and the Confederacy, Sk'ar enlisted T'Syriél along with Humans in order to give either side the impression the other had betrayed their peace.<ref name="aite">{{Hyperspace|url=hyperspace/member/insideronline/97/indexp4.html|series=Aliens in the Empire|text=Part 2: To a Traitor Go the Spoils}}</ref> A number of T'Syriél fought in specially fitted [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtrooper]] armor when Sk'ar launched his takeover attempt,<ref name="marvel53" /> only for Peacebringer, Longknife and elements of the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] to team up to foil Sk'ar's plan.<ref name="marvel54">[[Star Wars (1977) 54|''Star Wars'' (1977) 54]]</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
The T'Syriél first appeared in [[Star Wars (1977) 53|''Star Wars'' (1977) 53]], written by [[Chris Claremont]] and released in [[1981]]. Most of the art from ''Star Wars'' 53 and [[Star Wars (1977) 54|54]] was not originally intended for a ''[[Star Wars]]'' story&mdash;it was originally intended for [[Marvel Comics]]' ''[[Wikipedia:John Carter, Warlord of Mars|John Carter, Warlord of Mars]]'' series, which had been canceled in [[1979]]. Wanting to use 30 pages or so of fully-penciled artwork, Marvel had artist [[Carmine Infantino]] adapt the pages for ''Star Wars'', transforming the native Martians into the T'Syriél.<ref name="insider">{{InsiderCite|146|Authors of the Expanded Universe|Authors of the Expanded Universe: Chris Claremont}}</ref>

